articles.title: Stuck antenna freed on Jupiter-bound spacecraft - Phys.org
articles.description: A crucial radar antenna on a European spacecraft bound for Jupiter is no longer jammed.
articles.content:
A crucial radar antenna on a European spacecraft bound for Jupiter is no longer jammed.
Flight controllers in Germany freed the 52-foot (16-meter) antenna Friday after nearly a month of effort.
